                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-203-off1075 t18250915-203-crimeloc1078"></join>. Between four and five o'clock on the evening of the 25th of July, I saw the prisoner steal a piece of bacon from the window, while I was standing on the left side of the shop. I gave an alarm, pursued and came up with him, and took it from him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A woman dropped this bit of bacon, I took it up. I have a son now worth 1000 l. in Bermondsey parish - I never took any thing in my life.</p>
